content.description: Stand start right hand on a rail, left hand on a rail. Pull up and gain an overhanging foot to push over and match on the left rail, opening up your right foot for a heel hook on the start hold you just let go of. From here, reach high with your right, crimp, and pull to gain good feet. Move up the other 18 feet with some 5-9+ solo climbing.
content.protection: Pads. A bolt was found at the top.
content.location: This is on the south side of Overdue Boulder.

content.description: Make some awkward moves on sidepull slopers up, and work out the funky sequence.

This is the problem that goes directly up the steep face of Food Lube. It is mentioned by Kenny in the comments section of the Nine Style area. The problem starts from a low set of holds, right hand big pocket and left hand dish. Cross over with the left to the next large pocket and sort of dyno/deadpoint to the right hand 3 finger pocket. Get high feet, and make a 5-6 foot left hand movement to the crimp about 1 foot below the lip of the boulder. Make another big move with the right hand to the top of the boulder, and top out on good holds. This is one of the best problems at the grade that I have ever done. This thing is stout!
content.protection: Mash mats The landing is very flat and sandy.
content.location: It is on the North side of the Overdue Boulder on the 35 degree overhanging face.

content.description:
Start in pockets, move left, make a move to a sloper - deadpoint into a pocket, make a hard lockoff, and hit 2 small crimps before topping out.

The last set of crimps have been broken maybe upping the grade?? maybe, maybe not.

Check out the video to see the climb posted!
